author: app.com
title: Unbeaten Point Boro football outlasts Raritan
text:
MORE POINT PLEASANT - Junior wide receiver Hayden Frey 's preseason broken collar bone was a bad break in more ways than one. It came just as Frey was gearing up for what otherwise promised to be an exciting season at Point Pleasant Boro.
“When I got back, the orthopedic doctor said I healed as fast I could. I think that’s because I had to play this year,’’ Frey said after making seven catches Friday night, including one for a touchdown, as the No. 9 Panthers remained undefeated with a 33-27 victory over Raritan.
The Shore Conference nondivisional game left Point Boro with a 7-0 record for the first time since the program went 12-0 and won the South Group II championship in 2005.
Week 7: All the scores from Shore Conference football games
Frey was in top form in only his third game since returning to action, and the 23-yard touchdown pass he caught from Noah Husak with 7:27 left in the third quarter proved to be the game-winning points.
